      <h2 style="line-height: 1.25em">
        Major life changes: deeply in ~ LOVE ~, moving to
        American Continent, bringing more transparency to
        my work and all the economic activities in general
      </h2>
      <p>Dear friends,<br>
      I would like to share with all of you some major changes in my life. Almost a year ago, on
      January 9th, I met a wonderful woman name Carmen. We fallen in love at first sight and since
      that moment we shared together 9 beautiful months filled with blissful magic of love.</p>
      <img src="/assets/p+c+h.jpg" alt="pavlik <3 carmita" />
      <p style="text-align: center">Jan 10th, Tier Garten Berlin our very first walk together, we found a heart carved in the grass
      and took those photos (also sharing our first shy hug)</p>
      <p>Carmen came to European Continent to participate in exchange program, for people studying
      art, between Mexico City and Braunschweig. After we met we lived most of the time together.
      Big part of it in a cozy room she had rented in Braunschweig and some parts in Berlin staying
      with various friends, especially in famous from it hospitality IndieHaus (former Banana House).
      Originally Carmen planned to stay in Europe for just one semester but to my great joy she
      stayed for two \o/</p>
      <p>After she finished the second semester, we had time to travel together and visit Barcelona and
      Paris. In that time enjoying hospitality of friends who generously offered us places to stay.
      Finally in the very beginning of October, Carmen needed return back to Mexico City :’( for the
      last semester at the University where she studies art. Since then, we both miss each other very
      much and share together a dream to reunite again as soon as possible. I decided to simply
      move to Mexico City and this way answer the call of our hearts.</p>
      <p>To make it possible, I needed to start adjusting the lifestyle I practiced in last 6 years. First of all,
      crossing the Atlantic ocean, without carrying any state documents seemed like asking for a
      trouble. I could try it if I wanted to go there just to give a try doing it this way, but I don’t! Since I
      go there to live together with the woman I love, to make sure I arrive there safely and can stay
      for as long as we both feel like, I decided to accept state documents for some time again. While
      taking such compromise, I will still continue to participate in developing new generation of
      identity systems based on trust, our real social relationships and which leverage modern
      information technologies. Once we succeed in that work, the documents I just accepted will find
      their destination in appropriate recycling bins</p>
      <p>I also already asked three good friends James, Samuel and Daniel to help me with booking a
      flight to Mexico City in the first week of January. They accepted to help me with that so I prepare
      to fly there on January 8th \o/ This way we will also get to celebrate the first aniversary of meeting each other, togeher once again ~&lt;3~</p>
      <p>James also agreed to run small small crowdfunding campaign to distribute the expense related
      to buying the flight for me. I would like to ask everyone who feels like sharing this expense to
      help through the <a href="https://www.gofundme.com/aze7f6x8">crowdfunding campaign page</a></p>
      <p>Once I arrive to Mexico City, for the first 6 months when Carmen needs to finish her university
      we plan to rent a small humble studio, where we can live together with two cats, who she takes
      care of Zafiro and Akira :)</p>
