      <p>After that we will have more flexibility to look for other places to live together. Possibly outside of
      big city close to nature, as a part of an intentional and environment conscious community.</p>
      <p>I would still like to continue working on what I truly believe in, what strengthens our commons,
      what will benefit society as whole and do it without asking or accepting money for the work I do.
      At the same time, we share our lives with each other and now decisions which I made
      independently in a past also affect her well being. In next 6 months I would like to take time to
      open all such decisions and discuss them in depth with Carmen. This way we can start making
      together decisions for which we both take responsibility.</p>
      <p>In those first months, very likely we will not avoid having monetary expenses, we will publish
      exact calculations very soon but it seems around 9000 MXN / 500 EUR per month. This will
      include rent, utilities and basic food. Having them secured for first 3 or even whole 6 months
      would enable me to focus on the work I do and Carmen to finishing the university. We plan to
      honestly publish online details about every single expense. I will also link from those public logs
      to various alternative approaches, which in a future can secure the same needs but without
      depending on money.</p>
      <p>Carmen plans to start offering art and creativity classes to younger students from January.
      Asking them for financial support but also experimenting with <a href="https://github.com/hackers4peace/polyeconomy.info/wiki/Karma-Pass">karma pass</a> approach. During our
      stay in Europe, she paid for renting a room in which later we lived together very often, she also
      covered spendings for food which we couldn’t get from dumpster diving or foodsharing network.
      Right after arriving to Mexico City I will start working on supporting developments of Food
      Networks, which I hope very soon will provide fair, sustainable and stable ways for producing
      and consuming food ( <a href="https://news.vice.com/video/the-fruits-of-mexicos-cheap-labor">for everyone, not just us !</a>). While doing that, I would still like in first months
      take care of securing our basic needs through financial help from broad network of friends.</p>
      <p>To stay fully transparent about my economic activities, I plan to keep public logs of all my
      consumptions and contributions. If any of them relate to some flows of money, they will also
      stay publicly tracked and properly interlinked. I will also communicate in my work, how it should
      contribute to providing alternatives which don’t require such monetary flows. Every week I also
      plan to publish an online video with quick overview of my economic activities, similar to <a href="https://vimeo.com/channels/unmonpublicreviews">public reviews we did during pilot session of unMonastery Matera</a></p>
      <p>In next 6 months I plan to work on:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://valueflo.ws/">Value Flows</a></li>
        <li><a href="http://www.openfoodnetwork.org/">Open Food Network</a></li>
        <li><a href="http://unmonastery.org/">unMonastery</a></li>
        <li><a href="http://www.w3.org/Social/WG/">W3C Social WG</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/community/economy/"> W3C Social Economy CG</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/community/rdfjs/">W3C RDFJS CG</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://wwelves.org/">worldwide elves</a> (it will become one, out of many to come, public trackers/aggregators for
        wishes which people can publish indepedently anywhere on The Web)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>I warmly welcome support from everyone who feels like helping and have capacity to do it. Even
      more than money donations through this crowdfunding campaign , I would like to invite everyone
      to collaborate together on developing alternative ways, which will enable us all to manage our
      lives in near future without depending on money. I commit to give even more attention and
      dedicate even more time to cofacilitate
      such collaborations!</p>
